<dl id="n09075c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09075c">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09075c"> 75(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> mongoloid <small>Darkred</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n09075c"><li>FW 550.17 </li><li><a href="../../flex/rB/lexrB.htm#n09075c">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/rB/l39rB.htm#n09075c">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n09075c">MS BL 47482b-105v</ms> </li><li>JJA 58:078 <a name="rA2yd" href="../../ff/fdra/rda.htm#rB0yd">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/r/rB0yd.htm#n09075c">Draft: III&sect;3B.0+</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Pour &ldquo;&eacute;lire&rdquo; et &ldquo;r&eacute;prouver&rdquo;, il lui <font color="green">[= Dr Letourneau]</font> suffit de diviser l&apos;humanit&eacute; en trois groupes, caract&eacute;ris&eacute;s en partie par la coloration plus ou moins fonc&eacute;e de la peau, en partie par les indices anatomiques, mais surtout par leurs rapports &agrave; la civilisation et &agrave; l&apos;histoire: 1&deg; La race <i>noire</i> &hellip;. 2&deg; La race <i>jaune</i>, mongole ou <mark>mongolo&iuml;de</mark>, de beaucoup sup&eacute;rieure &agrave; la premi&egrave;re &hellip;. <br><font color="green">[Dr Letourneau]</font> to divide humanity into three groups, characterised in part by how dark the skin-colour is, in part by anatomical indices, but primarily by their relationships to civilisation and to history: 1) The black race &hellip; 2) The yellow race, Mongol or Mongoloid, which is much superior to the former &hellip; 3) The white race] <small> L&eacute;on Metchnikoff, <a name="LMCG" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LMCG"><cite title="source">La Civilisation et les grands fleuves Historiques</cite></a> (1889) 86</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
